oday! "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 15:27","book":"1Ki","chapter":15,"verse":27}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Hb obscure"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ki:14:15","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" will strike Israel so that they will "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"so that they will supplied for clarity"},{"kind":"text","text":" shake as a reed shakes in water. He will uproot Israel from this good soil that he gave to their ancestors. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 29:28","book":"Deu","chapter":29,"verse":28,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" He will scatter them beyond the Euphrates "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 15:29","book":"2Ki","chapter":15,"verse":29,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 17:6","book":"2Ki","chapter":17,"verse":6,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" because they made their Asherah poles, angering the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":". "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 34:14–15","book":"Exo","chapter":34,"verse":14,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 12:3","book":"Deu","chapter":12,"verse":3,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Dt 29:28","book":"Deu","chapter":29,"verse":28},{"label":"2Kg 15:29","book":"2Ki","chapter":15,"verse":29},{"label":"2Kg 17:6","book":"2Ki","chapter":17,"verse":6},{"label":"Ex 34:14–15","book":"Exo","chapter":34,"verse":14},{"label":"Dt 12:3","book":"Deu","chapter":12,"verse":3}],"footnotes":[{"marker":2,"text":"so that they will supplied for clarity"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ki:14:16","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He will give up Israel because of Jeroboam’s sins that he committed and caused Israel to commit.” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 12:28","book":"1Ki","chapter":12,"verse":28,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 13:34","book":"1Ki","chapter":13,"verse":34,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 15:30","book":"1Ki","chapter":15,"verse":30,"letter":"c"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 12:28","book":"1Ki","chapter":12,"verse":28},{"label":"1Kg 13:34","book":"1Ki","chapter":13,"verse":34},{"label":"1Kg 15:30","book":"1Ki","chapter":15,"verse":30}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ki:14:17","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then Jeroboam’s wife got up and left and went to Tirzah. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 15:33","book":"1Ki","chapter":15,"verse":33,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Sg 6:4","book":"Sng","chapter":6,"verse":4,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" As she was crossing the threshold of the house, the boy died. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 15:33","book":"1Ki","chapter":15,"verse":33},{"label":"Sg 6:4","book":"Sng","chapter":6,"verse":4}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ki:14:18","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He was buried, and all Israel mourned for him, according to the word of the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" he had spoken through his servant the prophet Ahijah. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 14:12","book":"1Ki","chapter":14,"verse":12,"letter":"a"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 14:12","book":"1Ki","chapter":14,"verse":12}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ki:14:19","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"As for the rest of the events of Jeroboam’s reign, how he waged war "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 14:30","book":"1Ki","chapter":14,"verse":30,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 13:2–20","book":"2Ch","chapter":13,"verse":2,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" and how he reigned, note that they are written in the Historical Record of Israel’s Kings. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 14:30","book":"1Ki","chapter":14,"verse":30},{"label":"2Ch 13:2–20","book":"2Ch","chapter":13,"verse":2}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ki:14:20","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The length of Jeroboam’s reign was twenty-two years. He rested with his ancestors, and his son Nadab became king in his place. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 15:25","book":"1Ki","chapter":15,"verse":25,"letter":"a"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 15:25","book":"1Ki","chapter":15,"verse":25}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ki:14:21","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Now Rehoboam, Solomon’s son, reigned in Judah. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 12:1","book":"1Ki","chapter":12,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" Rehoboam was forty-one years old when he became king; he reigned seventeen years in Jerusalem, the city where the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" had chosen from all the tribes of Israel to put his name. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 12:5","book":"Deu","chapter":12,"verse":5,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 9:3","book":"1Ki","chapter":9,"verse":3,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 11:32","book":"1Ki","chapter":11,"verse":32,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 11:36","book":"1Ki","chapter":11,"verse":36,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" Rehoboam’s mother’s name was Naamah the Ammonite. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 12:13","book":"2Ch","chapter":12,"verse":13,"letter":"f"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 12:1","book":"1Ki","chapter":12,"verse":1},{"label":"Dt 12:5","book":"Deu","chapter":12,"verse":5},{"label":"1Kg 9:3","book":"1Ki","chapter":9,"verse":3},{"label":"1Kg 11:32","book":"1Ki","chapter":11,"verse":32},{"label":"1Kg 11:36","book":"1Ki","chapter":11,"verse":36},{"label":"2Ch 12:13","book":"2Ch","chapter":12,"verse":13}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ki:14:22","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Judah did what was evil in the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"’s sight. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 17:19","book":"2Ki","chapter":17,"verse":19,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 12:1","book":"2Ch","chapter":12,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 12:14","book":"2Ch","chapter":12,"verse":14,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" They provoked him to jealous anger "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 32:21","book":"Deu","chapter":32,"verse":21,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" more than all that their ancestors had done with the sins they committed. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 17:19","book":"2Ki","chapter":17,"verse":19},{"label":"2Ch 12:1","book":"2Ch","chapter":12,"verse":1},{"label":"2Ch 12:14","book":"2Ch","chapter":12,"verse":14},{"label":"Dt 32:21","book":"Deu","chapter":32,"verse":21}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ki:14:23","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"They also built for themselves high places, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 3:2","book":"1Ki","chapter":3,"verse":2,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 12:31","book":"1Ki","chapter":12,"verse":31,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" sacred pillars, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 23:24","book":"Exo","chapter":23,"verse":24,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 16:21","book":"Deu","chapter":16,"verse":21,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" and Asherah poles on every high hill and under every green tree; "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 3:2","book":"1Ki","chapter":3,"verse":2},{"label":"1Kg 12:31","book":"1Ki","chapter":12,"verse":31},{"label":"Ex 23:24","book":"Exo","chapter":23,"verse":24},{"label":"Dt 16:21","book":"Deu","chapter":16,"verse":21}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ki:14:24","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"there were even male cult prostitutes in the land. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 23:17","book":"Deu","chapter":23,"verse":17,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" They imitated all the detestable practices of the nations the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" had dispossessed before the Israelites. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 23:24","book":"Exo","chapter":23,"verse":24,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 18:9","book":"Deu","chapter":18,"verse":9,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 16:3","book":"2Ki","chapter":16,"verse":3,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 17:15","book":"2Ki","chapter":17,"verse":15,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 21:2","book":"2Ki","chapter":21,"verse":2,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"3Jn 11","book":"3Jn","chapter":1,"verse":11,"letter":"g"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Dt 23:17","book":"Deu","chapter":23,"verse":17},{"label":"Ex 23:24","book":"Exo","chapter":23,"verse":24},{"label":"Dt 18:9","book":"Deu","chapter":18,"verse":9},{"label":"2Kg 16:3","book":"2Ki","chapter":16,"verse":3},{"label":"2Kg 17:15","book":"2Ki","chapter":17,"verse":15},{"label":"2Kg 21:2","book":"2Ki","chapter":21,"verse":2},{"label":"3Jn 11","book":"3Jn","chapter":1,"verse":11}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ki:14:25","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"In the fifth year of King Rehoboam, King Shishak of Egypt "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 11:40","book":"1Ki","chapter":11,"verse":40,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" went to war against Jerusalem. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 12:2–11","book":"2Ch","chapter":12,"verse":2,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 11:40","book":"1Ki","chapter":11,"verse":40},{"label":"2Ch 12:2–11","book":"2Ch","chapter":12,"verse":2}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ki:14:26","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He seized the treasuries of the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"’s temple and the treasuries of the royal palace. He took everything. He took all the gold shields that Solomon had made. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 10:16","book":"1Ki","chapter":10,"verse":16,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 10:16","book":"1Ki","chapter":10,"verse":16}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ki:14:27","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"King Rehoboam made bronze shields to replace them and committed them into the care of the captains of the guards "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Lit the runners"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 22:17","book":"1Sa","chapter":22,"verse":17,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 15:1","book":"2Sa","chapter":15,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" who protected the entrance to the king’s palace. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Sm 22:17","book":"1Sa","chapter":22,"verse":17},{"label":"2Sm 15:1","book":"2Sa","chapter":15,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Lit the runners"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ki:14:28","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Whenever the king entered the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"’s temple, the guards would carry the shields, then they would take them back to the armory. "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"Lit the chamber of the runners"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 10:17","book":"1Ki","chapter":10,"verse":17,"letter":"a"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 10:17","book":"1Ki","chapter":10,"verse":17}],"footnotes":[{"marker":2,"text":"Lit the chamber of the runners"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ki:14:29","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The rest of the events of Rehoboam’s reign, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 12:15–16","book":"2Ch","chapter":12,"verse":15,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" along with all his accomplishments, are written about in the Historical Record of Judah’s Kings. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Ch 12:15–16","book":"2Ch","chapter":12,"verse":15}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ki:14:30","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"There was war between Rehoboam and Jeroboam throughout their reigns. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 12:21","book":"1Ki","chapter":12,"verse":21,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 15:6","book":"1Ki","chapter":15,"verse":6,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 12:21","book":"1Ki","chapter":12,"verse":21},{"label":"1Kg 15:6","book":"1Ki","chapter":15,"verse":6}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:1Ki:14:31","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Rehoboam rested with his ancestors and was buried with his ancestors in the city of David. His mother’s name was Naamah the Ammonite. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 14:21","book":"1Ki","chapter":14,"verse":21,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" His son Abijam "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"= Abijah in 2Ch 13"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Kg 15:1","book":"1Ki","chapter":15,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 11:20","book":"2Ch","chapter":11,"verse":20,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 13:1–14:1","book":"2Ch","chapter":13,"verse":1,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" became king in his place."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Kg 14:21","book":"1Ki","chapter":14,"verse":21},{"label":"1Kg 15:1","book":"1Ki","chapter":15,"verse":1},{"label":"2Ch 11:20","book":"2Ch","chapter":11,"verse":20},{"label":"2Ch 13:1–14:1","book":"2Ch","chapter":13,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"= Abijah in 2Ch 13"}]}]},"cachedAt":1783099306880}